#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.RandomState.standard_t.rst:3
msgid ""
"From Dalgaard page 83 [R89f5270d198b-1]_, suppose the daily energy intake "
"for 11 women in kilojoules (kJ) is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.RandomState.standard_t.rst:9
msgid ""
"Does their energy intake deviate systematically from the recommended value "
"of 7725 kJ? Our null hypothesis will be the absence of deviation, and the "
"alternate hypothesis will be the presence of an effect that could be either "
"positive or negative, hence making our test 2-tailed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.RandomState.standard_t.rst:14
msgid ""
"Because we are estimating the mean and we have N=11 values in our sample, we "
"have N-1=10 degrees of freedom. We set our significance level to 95% and "
"compute the t statistic using the empirical mean and empirical standard "
"deviation of our intake. We use a ddof of 1 to base the computation of our "
"empirical standard deviation on an unbiased estimate of the variance (note: "
"the final estimate is not unbiased due to the concave nature of the square "
"root)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.RandomState.standard_t.rst:30
msgid ""
"We draw 1000000 samples from Student's t distribution with the adequate "
"degrees of freedom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.RandomState.standard_t.rst:37
msgid ""
"Does our t statistic land in one of the two critical regions found at both "
"tails of the distribution?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.RandomState.standard_t.rst:43
msgid ""
"The probability value for this 2-tailed test is about 1.83%, which is lower "
"than the 5% pre-determined significance threshold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.RandomState.standard_t.rst:46
msgid ""
"Therefore, the probability of observing values as extreme as our intake "
"conditionally on the null hypothesis being true is too low, and we reject "
"the null hypothesis of no deviation."
msgstr ""

